fcitx5-sinsebeolsik-p2 (0.1.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Bundle setup-fcitx5-trigger.sh as /usr/bin/sinsebeolsik-p2-setup-trigger
    so .deb users can register the Hangul keysym in fcitx5 without cloning
    the repo or curling a script from GitHub.

 -- Bogamie <bogamie02@gmail.com>  Fri, 01 May 2026 20:30:00 +0900

fcitx5-sinsebeolsik-p2 (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * Hangul automaton with Sinsebeolsik P2 simulator-verified behavior:
    no dokkaebibul, no auto-IEUNG, no jong cluster splitting on next vowel,
    real-vs-virtual jung distinction, ssang-jaeum via doubled cho keystroke.
  * TOML-driven keymap loadable from
    ~/.local/share/fcitx5/sinsebeolsik-p2/sinsebeolsik_p2.toml
    or /usr/share/fcitx5/sinsebeolsik-p2/sinsebeolsik_p2.toml,
    with embedded fallback compiled in.
  * Helper script setup-fcitx5-trigger.sh registers the Hangul keysym
    as a global IM trigger.

 -- Bogamie <bogamie02@gmail.com>  Fri, 01 May 2026 00:00:00 +0900
